                                                    <p class="card-text" style="font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif; font-size: 30px ; margin-left: -240px; margin-top: 50px; margin-right: 150px; line-height: 116.7%; text-align: center;">The only place to be, every other Saturday With the future of Stamford Bridge secure, Chelsea kick on and go continental, signing some of the most famous names in the game. A foreign legion mixed with loyal players from closer to home thrive, collecting winners' medals for the first time in a generation. Crowd numbers swell and having been denied entry to the very first European Cup nearly 50 years earlier, the Blues at last win a place in the biggest club competition of them all, beginning new rivalries which will grow dramatically in years to come...</p>
